                            <comment id="14010493" author="nravi" created="Wed, 28 May 2014 00:31:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Pull request: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/mahout/pull/4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/mahout/pull/4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14010629" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 28 May 2014 02:15:15 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user nishkamravi2 commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/mahout/pull/4#issuecomment-44354961&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/mahout/pull/4#issuecomment-44354961&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    JIRA: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1565&quot; title=&quot;add MR2 options to MAHOUT_OPTS in bin/mahout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-1565&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-1565&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1565&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1565&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012089" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 06:38:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Github user dlyubimov commented on the pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/mahout/pull/4#issuecomment-44496355&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/mahout/pull/4#issuecomment-44496355&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    looks benign to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Need review from folks that were working on Hadoop 2 integration, to make sure this is in line with the rest of the effort. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1565&quot; title=&quot;add MR2 options to MAHOUT_OPTS in bin/mahout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-1565&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-1565&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012095" author="smarthi" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 06:43:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It is benign indeed. We have been running the present trunk snapshot on Hadoop 2x without having to specify any of these options.  What do u think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gokhancapan&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gokhancapan&quot;&gt;Gokhan Capan&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;br/&gt;
Resolve this as &apos;Not a problem&apos; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012119" author="nravi" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 07:33:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Slight clarification: these options existed in bin/mahout for MR1 and not MR2. This is an attempt at making the two consistent.&lt;br/&gt;
Difference in configuration may lead an observer to conclude that MR1 and MR2 are performing differently for an application built against Mahout. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012126" author="gokhancapan" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 07:43:53 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think there is no point of configuring output compression, number of reducers, etc. for Mahout.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012132" author="nravi" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 07:52:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In that case, should the following be deleted from bin/mahout (lines 248-257)?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.min.split.size=512MB&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.map.child.java.opts=-Xmx4096m&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.reduce.child.java.opts=-Xmx4096m&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.output.compress=true&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.compress.map.output=true&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.map.tasks=1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dmapred.reduce.tasks=1&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dio.sort.factor=30&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    MAHOUT_OPTS=&quot;$MAHOUT_OPTS -Dio.sort.mb=1024&quot;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14012136" author="ssc" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 08:03:19 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d favor removing that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012140" author="gokhancapan" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 08:06:46 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, now I can read the patch properly. The MR1 versions of those configurations are already set in bin/mahout, and you&apos;re suggesting to add MR2 versions of them, too, right?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am personally not a fan of setting such configurations in Mahout, and I would remove them as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14012152" author="nravi" created="Thu, 29 May 2014 08:23:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Modified the PR to remove those options from both bin/mahout and bin/mahout.cmd. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016135" author="nravi" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 02:47:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Has this PR been merged yet?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14016378" author="gokhancapan" created="Tue, 3 Jun 2014 11:48:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;We agree, conceptually, but this needs some further testing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14019252" author="nravi" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2014 21:47:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Done some testing at our end. Performance seems to improve after those options are removed. Does Mahout have an automated testing infrastructure for PR&apos;s? If not, how will further testing be done and by who.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14048262" author="hudson" created="Mon, 30 Jun 2014 23:39:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in Mahout-Quality #2678 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2678/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Mahout-Quality/2678/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1565&quot; title=&quot;add MR2 options to MAHOUT_OPTS in bin/mahout&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-1565&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-1565&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Remove mapreduce-job-specific MAHOUT_OPTS (nishkamravi via gcapan): this closes apache/mahout#4 (gcapan: rev 37b85253981770b455bd9936cef23de460662483)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bin/mahout&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;bin/mahout.cmd&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
